<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,834]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,591,616]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named for the Tokay Gecko, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[881,1241,591,616]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Gekko" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gecko">
<emphasis box="[881,1030,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Gekko gecko</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[1050,1232,591,616]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="5" refId="ref59566" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema Naturae per Regna Tria Naturae, secundum Classes, Ordines, Genera, Species, cum Characteribus, Differentiis, Synonymis, Locis. Tomus I. Editio Decima Reformata. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae [= Stockholm], [4] + 823 + [5] pp." type="journal article" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, ต๊กแกุin Thai, a charismatic lizard species found throughout southeastern Asia. Treat as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,834]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,665,690]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks.</emphasis>
In 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, C." box="[354,514,665,690]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="135 - 224" refId="ref58098" refString="Chen, C. - w. (1957) A revision of the velvet ants or Mutillidae of China (Hymenoptera). Quarterly Journal of the Taiwan Museum, 10 (3 - 4), 135 - 224, 6 pls." type="book chapter" year="1957">Chen’s (1957)</bibRefCitation>
treatment, this species keys to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mickel" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[869,1080,665,690]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Bischoffitilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sauteri" subSpecies="lingnani">
<emphasis box="[869,1080,665,690]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B. sauteri lingnani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be separated from that species by having T4–5 with the setae mostly black and without a medial golden setal spots. In 
<bibRefCitation author="Mickel, C. E." box="[1254,1436,701,726]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="177 - 307" refId="ref59784" refString="Mickel, C. E. (1935) The mutillid wasps of the islands of the Pacific Ocean (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 83 (2), 177 - 307. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1935. tb 01207. x" type="journal article" year="1935">Mickel’s (1935)</bibRefCitation>
treatment, it keys to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zavattari 1913)" authorityName="Zavattari" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Zavattari" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[386,687,737,762]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Bischoffitilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malica">
<emphasis box="[386,495,737,762]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B. malica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zavattari, E." box="[510,678,737,762]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="19 - 42" refId="ref61871" refString="Zavattari, E. (1913) H. Sauter's Formosa-Ausbeute. Mutillidae (Hym.). Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 79 A (3), 19 - 42." type="journal article" year="1913">Zavattari 1913</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authority="(Zavattari 1913)" authorityName="Zavattari" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Zavattari" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[727,1043,737,762]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Bischoffitilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opipara">
<emphasis box="[727,848,738,761]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B. opipara</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zavattari, E." box="[864,1035,737,762]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="19 - 42" refId="ref61871" refString="Zavattari, E. (1913) H. Sauter's Formosa-Ausbeute. Mutillidae (Hym.). Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, 79 A (3), 19 - 42." type="journal article" year="1913">Zavattari 1913</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, depending on how one scores the presence of lateral mesosomal teeth; 
<taxonomicName authority="Williams &amp; Lelej &amp; Okayasu &amp; Borkent &amp; Malee &amp; Thoawan &amp; Thaochan, 2019" authorityName="Williams &amp; Lelej &amp; Okayasu &amp; Borkent &amp; Malee &amp; Thoawan &amp; Thaochan" authorityYear="2019" box="[562,654,773,798]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Bischoffitilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tokay" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[562,654,773,798]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B. tokay</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[660,749,773,798]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[660,749,773,798]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be recognized by having T3 with a large transverse white setal patch.
</paragraph>
